text.Taxonomy and naming:
The species was first formally described by Robert Chinnock in 2007 and the description was published in Eremophila and Allied Genera: A Monograph of the Plant Family Myoporaceae. The specific epithet (jucunda) is a Latin word meaning "pleasant", "agreeable" or "delightful".Two subspecies are recognized in the Australian Plant Census:

Eremophila jucunda subsp. jucunda which has cream-coloured to lilac flowers, bright yellow hairs on the young branches, leaves and sepals, and hairs on the outside of the petal tube;
Eremophila jucunda subsp. pulcherrima which has lilac-coloured to light purple flowers, grey hairs on the young growth and petals which are glabrous on the outside.
